<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-03T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-03T15:00:00-05:00" n="418" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/3057: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Woodward</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-03T16:00:00-04:00">May 3,
                                    1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>994. Cuenca<note n="74" xml:id="d418fn74">Humberto Cuenca, Manager of the
                                Central Bank of Bolivia.</note> mentioned to Ashton<note n="75" xml:id="d418fn75">Anthony Ashton, of the British Legation in
                                Bolivia.</note> of the British Legation that Baldivieso had stated
                            that the Provisional Government would probably <pb facs="0469" n="455" xml:id="pg_455"/> promptly release the persons accused of plotting a
                            revolution and raise the state of siege if the Provisional Government
                            were to be recognized.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodward</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>